<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:20:41 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>哥伦比亚计划对数十只“可卡因河马”实施安乐死，这些河马是臭名昭著的毒贩巴勃罗·埃斯科瓦尔带来的动物后裔</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/colombia-plans-to-euthanize-dozens-of-cocaine-hippos-descendants-of-animals-brought-by-notorious-drug-trafficker-pablo-escobar-180988548/</link><description>如果不采取措施控制这些入侵生物，官员们估计到 2035 年，该物种的数量可能会增加到 1,000 只。因此，他们的目标是在今年晚些时候扑杀约 80 只。</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 21:15:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/colombia-plans-to-euthanize-dozens-of-cocaine-hippos-descendants-of-animals-brought-by-notorious-drug-trafficker-pablo-escobar-180988548/</guid></item><item><title>这位出生于佃农家庭的雕塑艺术家克服歧视成为“植物界的毕加索”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/born-to-a-family-of-sharecroppers-this-topiary-artist-overcame-discrimination-to-become-the-picasso-of-plants-180988544/</link><description>自学成才的艺术家 Pearl Fryar 本月去世，享年 86 岁，他的职业生涯始于试图赢得当地花园俱乐部的奖项。他最终成为园艺界的名人</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 19:44:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/born-to-a-family-of-sharecroppers-this-topiary-artist-overcame-discrimination-to-become-the-picasso-of-plants-180988544/</guid></item><item><title>长期被误认，这件海豹牙吊坠是由大约 15,000 年前的史前人类精心制作的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/long-misidentified-this-seal-tooth-pendant-was-carefully-crafted-by-a-prehistoric-human-roughly-15000-years-ago-180988543/</link><description>这件文物于 1867 年被发现，提出了关于旧石器时代晚期晚期居住在英格兰西南部的马格达林人的新理论</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 18:23:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/long-misidentified-this-seal-tooth-pendant-was-carefully-crafted-by-a-prehistoric-human-roughly-15000-years-ago-180988543/</guid></item><item><title>美国西部最具标志性的鸟类之一正试图在危险的机场附近交配。机器鸟能帮助拯救它们吗？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/one-of-the-american-wests-most-iconic-birds-is-attempting-to-mate-near-a-dangerous-airport-could-robo-birds-help-save-them-180988542/</link><description>环保人士正在部署跳舞的电子动画鸟，以引诱雄性大圣松鸡离开杰克逊霍尔机场，那里有数十只这种生物被飞机击中并杀死。</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/one-of-the-american-wests-most-iconic-birds-is-attempting-to-mate-near-a-dangerous-airport-could-robo-birds-help-save-them-180988542/</guid></item><item><title>从闪闪发光的头饰到柔和的帽子，新白金汉宫展览庆祝伊丽莎白二世的时尚</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-sparkling-tiaras-pastel-hats-new-buckingham-palace-exhibition-celebrates-fashion-elizabeth-ii-180988526/</link><description>英国女王不仅是世界领袖，还是时尚偶像。伊丽莎白故居举办的一场新秀突出了一些最令人难忘的造型及其背后的历史</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:00:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-sparkling-tiaras-pastel-hats-new-buckingham-palace-exhibition-celebrates-fashion-elizabeth-ii-180988526/</guid></item><item><title>国家美术馆为美国 250 岁生日举起一面艺术镜子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-holds-an-artistic-mirror-up-to-the-united-states-for-its-big-250th-birthday-180988538/</link><description>为了庆祝今年的五十周年纪念，“亲爱的美国”通过可追溯至 18 世纪末的艺术品来审视这个国家的土地、社区和革命历史</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-holds-an-artistic-mirror-up-to-the-united-states-for-its-big-250th-birthday-180988538/</guid></item><item><title>在主要音乐发布日，开车时要格外警惕。当顶级艺术家推出新专辑时，车祸死亡人数似乎激增</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/on-major-music-release-days-stay-extra-vigilant-while-driving-car-crash-deaths-seem-to-spike-when-top-artists-drop-new-albums-180988541/</link><description>一项新研究发现大专辑发行天数与交通死亡人数之间存在相关性。虽然研究无法证明新音乐导致了事故，但这项研究暗示了驾驶时的主要干扰因素</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 14:37:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/on-major-music-release-days-stay-extra-vigilant-while-driving-car-crash-deaths-seem-to-spike-when-top-artists-drop-new-albums-180988541/</guid></item><item><title>战争让人感觉超现实。看看这位美国摄影记者如何捕捉二战的恐怖和黑色幽默</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/war-can-feel-surreal-see-how-american-photojournalist-lee-miller-captured-horrors-dark-humor-world-war-ii-180988523/</link><description>一本重新发现的剪贴簿展示了英国《Vogue》战地记者李·米勒 (Lee Miller) 从未见过的照片，他跟随美国军队穿越欧洲</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 12:04:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/war-can-feel-surreal-see-how-american-photojournalist-lee-miller-captured-horrors-dark-humor-world-war-ii-180988523/</guid></item><item><title>墨西哥这座具有千年历史的祭坛属于阿兹特克人之前繁荣的文明</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-millennium-old-sacrificial-altar-in-mexico-belonged-to-a-civilization-that-thrived-before-the-aztecs-180988539/</link><description>这件被人类头骨包围的文物是在墨西哥中部托尔特克人的首都遗址在新铁路项目建设之前发现的</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 11:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-millennium-old-sacrificial-altar-in-mexico-belonged-to-a-civilization-that-thrived-before-the-aztecs-180988539/</guid></item><item><title>这种近 3 亿年前的木乃伊爬行动物揭示了我们呼吸方式的进化起源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-300-million-year-old-mummified-fossil-reveals-the-origins-of-breathing-in-amniotes-180988521/</link><description>保存异常完好的化石提供了已知最早的证据，证明陆地脊椎动物可以利用肋骨之间的肌肉将空气泵入和泵出胸部，这与现代哺乳动物、爬行动物和鸟类所使用的策略相同</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 20:06:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-300-million-year-old-mummified-fossil-reveals-the-origins-of-breathing-in-amniotes-180988521/</guid></item><item><title>令人眼花缭乱的带有单护栏的螺旋楼梯曾经通往埃菲尔铁塔的顶部。现在，您可以购买 14 个原始台阶</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-dizzying-spiral-staircase-with-a-single-guardrail-once-led-to-the-top-of-the-eiffel-tower-now-you-can-buy-14-of-the-original-steps-180988535/</link><description>连接塔楼第二层和第三层的 1,062 级台阶于 1889 年安装。有 137 年历史的楼梯碎片可以在几家法国博物馆找到</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 18:08:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-dizzying-spiral-staircase-with-a-single-guardrail-once-led-to-the-top-of-the-eiffel-tower-now-you-can-buy-14-of-the-original-steps-180988535/</guid></item><item><title>这幅阿尔泰米西娅·真蒂莱斯基的画作在地窖里卷了几十年，现在正在拍卖。为什么抹大拉的玛丽亚的脸从肖像中消失了？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/rolled-up-in-a-cellar-for-decades-this-artemisia-gentileschi-painting-is-now-up-for-auction-why-is-mary-magdalenes-face-missing-from-the-portrait-180988537/</link><description>这件艺术品在柏林发现，可能在第二次世界大战后的混乱中遭到损坏。尽管画布上有一个大洞，但本月晚些时候它的售价可能高达 180,000 美元</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 17:10:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/rolled-up-in-a-cellar-for-decades-this-artemisia-gentileschi-painting-is-now-up-for-auction-why-is-mary-magdalenes-face-missing-from-the-portrait-180988537/</guid></item><item><title>泼水节是泰国泼水的新年节日，每个人都拿出超级浸泡器，准备全身湿透</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-how-thailand-splashes-into-spring-with-songkran-a-new-years-water-festival-starting-april-13-180988536/</link><description>这一令人难忘的传统有着深厚的文化历史，植根于佛教，并因其喧闹的打水仗而在全球日益声名狼藉。</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 16:38:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-how-thailand-splashes-into-spring-with-songkran-a-new-years-water-festival-starting-april-13-180988536/</guid></item><item><title>首先，这种个性化细胞疗法治疗了一名患者的三种危及生命的自身免疫性疾病</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-this-personalized-cell-therapy-treated-three-life-threatening-autoimmune-diseases-in-one-patient-180988528/</link><description>患者卧床不起，需要每天输血，她尝试了九种不同的疗法，但没有带来持久的效果。因此，研究人员修改了她的一些免疫细胞，以便它们攻击她有缺陷的细胞</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-this-personalized-cell-therapy-treated-three-life-threatening-autoimmune-diseases-in-one-patient-180988528/</guid></item><item><title>这部反战杰作属于哪里？在西班牙，借用毕加索《格尔尼卡》的请求引发激烈争论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/where-does-this-anti-war-masterpiece-belong-in-spain-a-request-to-borrow-picassos-guernica-sparks-a-bitter-debate-180988533/</link><description>这件艺术品描绘了 1937 年巴斯克村庄遭受的轰炸。现在，搬迁争论引发了如何平衡这幅画的文化意义和保护需求的问题</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/where-does-this-anti-war-masterpiece-belong-in-spain-a-request-to-borrow-picassos-guernica-sparks-a-bitter-debate-180988533/</guid></item><item><title>奴隶和自由工人用砖块建造了托马斯·杰斐逊的蒙蒂塞洛。考古学家刚刚发现了他们使用的窑炉之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/workers-built-thomas-jeffersons-monticello-brick-by-brick-archaeologists-just-discovered-one-of-the-kilns-they-used-180988525/</link><description>研究人员认为，新出土的结构在 1770 年代初建造该地点的原始宅邸时被用来烧制和固化砖块</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2026 10:00:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/workers-built-thomas-jeffersons-monticello-brick-by-brick-archaeologists-just-discovered-one-of-the-kilns-they-used-180988525/</guid></item><item><title>阿耳忒弥斯 2 号宇航员在完成历史性绕月任务后成功返回地球</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/artemis-2-astronauts-successfully-return-to-earth-after-completing-a-historic-mission-around-the-moon-180988513/</link><description>宇航员们在十天的旅程中打破了太空飞行记录并观察到了人类从未见过的月球特征，并于周五落水。这标志着 50 多年来首次有人离开地球轨道</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/artemis-2-astronauts-successfully-return-to-earth-after-completing-a-historic-mission-around-the-moon-180988513/</guid></item><item><title>这些野生黑猩猩已经在“内战”中战斗了近十年。这是同类中最血腥的分裂</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-wild-chimps-have-been-fighting-in-a-civil-war-for-nearly-a-decade-its-the-bloodiest-split-ever-seen-among-their-kind-180988527/</link><description>乌干达的恩戈戈黑猩猩已经分裂成两个主要派系，自 2018 年分裂以来，已有数十人死亡。一项新的研究详细描述了前所未有的暴力行为，这可能有助于揭示人类战争的进化基础</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 20:12:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-wild-chimps-have-been-fighting-in-a-civil-war-for-nearly-a-decade-its-the-bloodiest-split-ever-seen-among-their-kind-180988527/</guid></item><item><title>这幅文森特·梵高的画被发现包裹在宜家袋子和血迹斑斑的枕头中。现在，这件艺术品已恢复昔日的辉煌</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-vincent-van-gogh-painting-was-found-wrapped-in-an-ikea-bag-and-a-blood-stained-pillow-now-the-artwork-has-been-restored-to-its-former-glory-180988530/</link><description>艺术侦探阿瑟·布兰德 (Arthur Brand) 于 2023 年找回了《春天的纽南牧师住宅花园》(The Parsonage Garden at Nuenen in Spring)，距其从荷兰博物馆被盗三年后。经过精心修复，画布现在重新展出</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 19:00:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-vincent-van-gogh-painting-was-found-wrapped-in-an-ikea-bag-and-a-blood-stained-pillow-now-the-artwork-has-been-restored-to-its-former-glory-180988530/</guid></item><item><title>经过近 80 年的怀疑，科学家表示插在大象肋骨之间的矛提供了尼安德特人狩猎大型动物的证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-nearly-80-years-of-doubt-scientists-say-a-spear-lodged-between-elephant-ribs-offers-evidence-that-neanderthals-hunted-big-game-180988522/</link><description>1948年，业余考古学家发掘了这些遗骸，这应该改变了研究人员对尼安德特人的看法。但糟糕的记录在科学界引起了怀疑</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 16:05:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-nearly-80-years-of-doubt-scientists-say-a-spear-lodged-between-elephant-ribs-offers-evidence-that-neanderthals-hunted-big-game-180988522/</guid></item></channel></rss>